b>b</b>, with direction such that the ordered set (<b>a</b>, <b>b</b>, <b>n=
</b>) is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orientation_(vector_space=
)" title=3D"Orientation (vector space)">positively oriented</a>.</li></ul><=
/div>
<p>If the vectors <b>a</b> and <b>b</b> are parallel (that is, the angle <i=
>=CE=B8</i> between them is either 0=C2=B0 or 180=C2=B0), by the above form=
ula, the cross product of <b>a</b> and <b>b</b> is the <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zero_vector" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Zero vecto=
r">zero vector</a> <b>0</b>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Direction">Direction</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCross_product&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Direction"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-left" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Cross_product.gif" class=3D"mw=
