</p><p>The above-mentioned triple product expansion (bac=E2=80=93cab rule) =
can be easily proven using this notation.
</p><p>As mentioned above, the Lie algebra <b>R</b><sup>3</sup> with cross =
product is isomorphic to the Lie algebra <b>so(3)</b>, whose elements can b=
e identified with the 3=C3=973 skew-symmetric matrices. The map <b>a</b> =
=E2=86=92 [<b>a</b>]<sub>=C3=97</sub> provides an isomorphism between <b>R<=
/b><sup>3</sup> and <b>so(3)</b>. Under this map, the cross product of 3-ve=
ctors corresponds to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commutato=
r" title=3D"Commutator">commutator</a> of 3x3 skew-symmetric matrices.
</p>
